tag_professor: Tough Grader (2)  Participation matters (2)  Inspirational (1)  GRADED BY FEW THINGS (1)
comments: I personally did not enjoy the class and when she did not agree with you she made it very known. However, I can appreciate her teaching style but the solely peer-discussion based platform did not work for me. As well, I got an A on every assignment and still got a B+ in the class (and yes I did participate).

tag_professor: Tough Grader (2)  Participation matters (2)  Inspirational (1)  GRADED BY FEW THINGS (1)
comments: Professor Cadavid is awesome and always willing to help. The classes are discuss-oriented.

tag_professor: Tough Grader (2)  Participation matters (2)  Inspirational (1)  GRADED BY FEW THINGS (1)
comments: One of the best Humanities teachers to have. She keeps the class engaging and interesting, but encourages a lot of class participation so speak up at least once per class if you\'re on the shy side.

tag_professor: Tough Grader (2)  Participation matters (2)  Inspirational (1)  GRADED BY FEW THINGS (1)
comments: Good professor who is willing to help and prioritizes constructive discussions. Sometimes she will try too hard to make her students reach her thought process that she actually ends up confusing the class. Other than that, she is overall very helpful and will give you the grade you deserve.

tag_professor: Tough Grader (2)  Participation matters (2)  Inspirational (1)  GRADED BY FEW THINGS (1)
comments: Dr. Cadavid is an engaging and helpful professor. You need to be able to speak up in class to be receptive to her though, which some students struggle with. Her class is very discussion oriented and though she seems disorganized at times she is not too difficult to follow.

tag_professor: Tough Grader (2)  Participation matters (2)  Inspirational (1)  GRADED BY FEW THINGS (1)
comments: My favorite professor I have ever had. So fun, so helpful, and keeps you engaged the ENTIRE time. Love her.

tag_professor: Tough Grader (2)  Participation matters (2)  Inspirational (1)  GRADED BY FEW THINGS (1)
comments: Love her! She kind of has low expectations, and if you speak in class and appear to try, you\'ll do great!

tag_professor: Tough Grader (2)  Participation matters (2)  Inspirational (1)  GRADED BY FEW THINGS (1)
comments: I\'ve had Professor Cadavid several times. I believe she has a solid grasp of her specialty subjects (Ancient, Aristotle, epistemology, 20th Analytic), but lacks the ability to confer her knowledge in a clear and consistent manner. Also, she ends up losing track of the syllabus as she lets the students decide the pace of the course.
